<!--
    PUF France Use Case 9: Payment to Third Party - Distributor/Agent
    (Facture à payer à un tiers qui gère aussi la commande/réception - Distributeur/Dépositaire)
    
    Business Scenario:
    - Third party (distributor/agent) manages commercial functions: ordering, receipt, invoicing
    - Third party receives payment on behalf of SELLER
    - NOT factoring - no legal transfer of receivable ownership
    - Distributor acts as commercial intermediary, not financial institution
    
    Key Differences from UC8 (Factoring):
    - Invoice type 380 (standard commercial), NOT 393 (factored)
    - NO subrogation/assignment notice (BT-21="ACC")
    - Role qualification "PE" (Payee), NOT "DL" (Factor)
    - Simplified workflow - replication to third party not mandatory
    
    Key Requirements:
    - Business process B1: Standard invoice
    - Invoice type code: 380 (Standard commercial invoice)
    - BG-10 PAYEE: Distributor information (BT-59, BT-60, BT-61)
    - EXT-FR-FE-26: "PE" (Payee - distributor receives payment)
    - BG-17 Payment: Distributor's IBAN (BT-84)
    - NO BT-21 "ACC" subrogation notice
    - Amount due payable to Distributor
    
    Financial Flow:
    - Invoice total: 4500.00 EUR (net) + 900.00 EUR VAT = 5400.00 EUR
    - BUYER pays: 5400.00 EUR to Distributor
    - Distributor manages: Commercial relationship and payment collection
    - Distributor remits: Payment to SELLER (minus commission, per separate agreement)
    
    Workflow:
    1. SELLER creates e-invoice with Distributor as PAYEE
    2. BUYER receives invoice via PPF platform
    3. BUYER pays Distributor directly (Distributor's IBAN in BT-84)
    4. Distributor receives payment from BUYER
    5. Distributor notifies SELLER of payment receipt
    6. SELLER posts "Encaissée" status when Distributor confirms settlement
    
    French Text Codes (BT-21/BT-22):
    - #REG#: Company legal form and share capital
    - #ABL#: Trade register number (RCS)
    - #AAI#: APE business activity code
    - #PMD#: Late payment penalties (payable to Distributor)
    - #PMT#: Fixed collection costs indemnity (€40 - payable to Distributor)
    - #BAR#: Treatment type (B2B e-invoicing)
    - NO ACC: No subrogation notice (not factoring)
-->
